thread.title: Boys roundup, Oct. 8

author: Staff reports
title: Boys roundup, Oct. 8
text:
Soccer RCAC
McQuaid 2, Edison 0
Alessandro Margiotta and Justin LaFountain each scored for McQuaid to lift the Knights 2-0 over Edison in an RCAC soccer game Thursday.
Adriano Margiotta and Justin Salamone earned the assists for McQuaid (9-2-2).
Franklin 4, School of the Arts 1
Shakr Asad tallied two goals and two assists in the win for Franklin (2-9).
Esam Saleh had one goal and one assist for the Quakers.
World of Inquiry 2, Wilson 0
Michael Hunter made seven saves to earn the shutout for Inquiry (10-2-1).
Non-league
Finney 12, Rochester Academy Charter 0
Alex Vega scored three goals and broke the single-season goal record for Finney (8-4).
Aquinas 5, East 1
Luke Putnam scored off an assist from Dylan Martinez and David Giallanza added another with the assist from Justin Pumputis for Aquinas (4-9-1). Kyle Pero also scored for the Little Irish.
Livingston County
Mount Morris 3, Pavilion/York 2
Reed Goho scored the game-winning goal in the 72nd minute to lift Mount Morris (9-4).
Goho finished the game with two goals.
Brendan Maldonado recorded one goal and one assist for the Blue Devils.
Avon 3, Letchworth 0
Jake Peterson, Cam Hughes and Sam Bond each scored a goal for Avon (3-9-1).
Brandon Gingher made five saves to complete the shutout for the Braves.
Letchworth is 2-11.
Wayland-Cohocton 4, Dansville 2
Michael Schumacher and Kalum Holbrook each scored two goals for W-C (7-8).
Nick Vogler and Vito Blonco each scored a goal for Danville (6-7).
Livonia 2, Hornell 0
Kyle Feldman scored both goals for Livonia (11-1).
Geneseo 3, Le Roy 1
Josh Welch, Ethan Roth and Sean Kelly each tallied goals for Geneseo (11-1).
Perry 3, Warsaw 1
Edwi Rojo tallied two goals and Mason Bush added one goal and one assist for Perry (7-6-1).
Wayland-Cohocton 4, Dansville 2
Michael Schumacher and Kalum Holbrook each scored two goals for Way-Co.
Finger Lakes
Bloomfield 3, Midlakes 0
Jimmy Hart, Dalton Phillips and Christian Eveleigh each scored for Bloomfield.
Genesee Region
Wheatland-Chili 3, Pembroke 0
Ben Gebhardt tallied two goals and Curtis Williams added one goal and one assist for W-C (9-3-1).
Finger Lakes Region
Newark 2, Geneva 0
Will Gibson scored two goals and Forrest Blondell added an assist for Newark (5-8-1).
Volleyball
Monroe County
Brighton 25-25-25, Webster 8-22-21
Ben Delacruz had 16 kills, 2 blocks and 2 aces and Tristan Judd ha7 kills, 6 blocks and 5 aces for Brighton (10-2).
Connor Spiegel tallied 10 kills for Webster (7-5).
Rush-Henrietta 25-23-25-25, Canadagua 21-25-18-19
Matthew Zarzycki had 24 assists and 11 digs and Jeffrey Cardot added 13 kills, 28 assists and seven digs for R-H (5-8).
RCAC
World of Inquiry 25-25-17-27, Leadership Academy 10-21-25-25
Ceyquan Salmon recorded 10 service points and Isaiah Shepard added 11 service points and nine kills for Inquiry (4-7).
East 25-25-25, NE/NE College Prep 18-20-21
Eddie Casado tallied 12 service points and Egardo Quinones had seven kills for East (10-2).
